            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-indigo-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">5</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xl">Carrier logos visible: 43% more qualified prospects</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2 leading-relaxed">Agent represented major carriers but buried this info. Added "We represent: State Farm, Progressive, Allstate, USAA" logos prominently on homepage. Month 1: 43% more qualified quote requests. Visible carriers = legitimacy = choice = trust. Shoppers see carrier logos = legitimate agent = quote request.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-indigo-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">6</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xl">Response timeÊâøËØ∫: 89% higher conversion to policy</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2 leading-relaxed">Agent added "We Respond Within 2 Hours - Guaranteed" badge next to quote form. Auto-responder confirms: "Received your request, David will call by [time]." Month 1: 89% higher conversion from quote request to policy sold. Insurance shopping = urgent = competitor quotes arriving fast. Fast responseÊâøËØ∫ = you're responsive = hire you.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MY EXPERIENCE: DAVID PARK CASE STUDY -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-5xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">MY EXPERIENCE</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">David Park, "Park Insurance Services" - Austin, TX (12 years in business)</p>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-slate-50 border-[3px] border-indigo-300 p-8 md:p-10 rounded-lg">
        <p class="text-sm font-black text-indigo-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE BEFORE: 18 QUOTE REQUESTS/MONTH, $8,400 COMMISSION</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">Park's website: 2017 template, stock photos of happy families, value proposition vague ("Protecting What Matters Most"), license number buried in footer, quote form 5 steps with 23 fields. No carrier logos visible. Mobile: form unusable. Blog: empty. Park: "I've been selling insurance for 12 years. I know my stuff. But my website looked like I started yesterday. People searching for insurance visited 10 agent sites, saw my outdated design, assumed I wasn't established, requested quotes from competitors. I was losing prospects to agents with worse products but better websites."</p>

        <p class="text-sm font-black text-indigo-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE FIX: ONE WEEKEND, $2,100</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">Friday: chose Webflow (compliance control needed for carrier approvals). Sunday night: launched new site with 1) "Licensed in Texas - #9876543" badge prominent, 2) one-page quote form (6 fields: name, email, phone, coverage type, ZIP, "best time to call"), 3) carrier logos (State Farm, Progressive, Allstate, USAA, Liberty Mutual) on homepage, 4) "We Respond Within 2 Hours" badge, 5) mobile-optimized form (large buttons, big text), 6) insurance blog with 12 helpful articles, 7) coverage explanations (auto, home, life, umbrella), 8) real client testimonials with names/policy types.</p>

        <p class="text-sm font-black text-indigo-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE AFTER: 94 QUOTE REQUESTS/MONTH, $28,800 COMMISSION, 243% INCREASE</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">Month 1: 52 quote requests (up from 18, 189% increase), $14,400 commission. License visible: legitimacy established = trust = quotes. One-page form: 73% completion vs 13% before. Carrier logos: shoppers recognized carriers = qualified requests. ResponseÊâøËØ∫: 89% conversion to policies sold. Mobile form: 67% requests from phones. Blog: 8 organic leads from search. Park: "Family searched 'home insurance Austin,' found my blog post 'How Much Home Insurance Do You Need?' They read it, trusted my expertise, requested quote. I sold them $2,400/year policy. Before: invisible. After: content brings prospects. Best $2,100 I ever spent."</p>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-indigo-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white/70 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-indigo-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Month 1:</strong> 52 quote requests, $14,400 commission, 189% increase. License visible + simple form + carrier logos = immediate results.<br><strong>Month 2:</strong> 73 quote requests, $21,600 commission. Added 8 more blog articles + client testimonials.<br><strong>Month 3:</strong> 94 quote requests, $28,800 commission. Blog driving 22 organic leads/month. 243% total increase in 90 days. Investment: $2,100. ROI: 1,271%.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-indigo-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-5xl">
