      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">6 Website Mistakes Killing Insurance Agent Sales (And How to Fix Them)</p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Mistake 1: License number hidden or buried</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Agent puts license in footer (nobody clicks). Homepage says nothing about credentials. Shopper doesn't know if you're legitimate = they leave. <strong>Fix:</strong> Add "Licensed in [State] - License #XYZ" badge prominently near header. Results: One agent saw 4x more quote requests in 30 days. Visible licensing = legitimacy = trust = quotes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Mistake 2: Complicated multi-step quote forms</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Agent has 5-step form with 23 fields. Shopper wants quick quote, faces questionnaire = abandons form. <strong>Fix:</strong> One-page form with essential fields: name, email, phone, coverage type, ZIP code. Call them for details. Results: One agent went from 13% to 73% form completion. Simple form = more quotes = more sales.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Mistake 3: No carrier logos or representation</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Agent represents major carriers but never displays logos. Shopper doesn't know if you're legitimate or if they'll have carrier choice. <strong>Fix:</strong> Add "We represent: [Carrier Logos]" prominently on homepage. Results: 43% more qualified quote requests. Visible carriers = legitimacy = choice.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Mistake 4: No educational content (blog)</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Shoppers search "how much home insurance do I need?" but find nothing helpful from you. They find competitor's blog instead. <strong>Fix:</strong> Publish weekly helpful content: coverage explanations, claim tips, cost guides. Results: One agent went from 2 to 15 organic leads/month after blog. Content = organic traffic = free leads.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Mistake 5: No response timeÊâøËØ∫</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Shopper submits quote request, waits 24 hours for response. Meanwhile, 3 competitors called within 2 hours. Who gets the sale? <strong>Fix:</strong> Add "We Respond Within 2 Hours - Guaranteed" badge. Auto-responder confirms. Results: 89% higher conversion to policy sold. Fast response = you're responsive = hire you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Mistake 6: Non-existent mobile quote form</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">67% of insurance searches happen on phones (crisis = immediate search). Form unusable on mobile = they can't request quotes. <strong>Fix:</strong> Mobile-optimized form. Test on your phone. Large buttons, big text, minimal fields. Results: One agent went from 19% to 71% mobile quote completion after optimization. Mobile = quote requests.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TOOL COMPARISONS -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
