    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-5xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Webflow AI for Insurance Agents</h2>

      <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-indigo-300 p-8 md:p-10 rounded-lg">
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Why Webflow Wins for Compliance Control</p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Custom Carrier Disclaimers</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Webflow gives you full control over footer content. Add state-required disclaimers: "Not affiliated with or endorsed by [Carrier Name]." Each state has different requirements. Webflow lets you customize per state without platform restrictions. Carrier compliance departments require this. Squarespace/Wix limit footer customization.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">2. State-Specific Licensing Display</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Agents licensed in multiple states need different license numbers displayed based on visitor location. Webflow's CMS + JavaScript can show relevant license: "Licensed in Texas - #9876543" for Texas visitors, "Licensed in California - #1234567" for California visitors. Compliance requires accurate licensing display.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Professional Portfolio Feel</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Clean, modern designs communicate stability. Insurance is about trust. Outdated website = risky agent = they leave. Webflow's professional templates (or custom designs) establish credibility. Shoppers see polished site = established agent = trust = quote request.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Lightning-Fast PageSpeed</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Clean code, optimized images. 95+ PageSpeed scores (vs. 60-80 for Wix). Google rewards fast sites with higher rankings. Mobile searchers abandon slow forms. Speed = quote completions. Insurance shoppers are impatient. Slow form = abandonment = lost lead.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">5. CMS for Insurance Content</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Create blog content, coverage guides, FAQ articles. Organize by category (auto, home, life, business). Add custom fields: coverage type, reading time, related articles. One agent built 50-article blog library driving 30+ organic leads/month. Content = organic traffic = free leads.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-indigo-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-indigo-50 rounded-r mt-8">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Best For:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Insurance agents with carrier compliance requirements, multi-state licensing, content marketing focus. Requires 2-3 day build time or hire Webflow designer ($500-2,000). Not for beginners.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DETAILED BREAKDOWN: SQUARESPACE -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-5xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Squarespace AI for Insurance Agents</h2>

